cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

The paper proposes a new mechanism for improving the efficiency of residual networks, which are commonly used in computer vision tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves designing a novel inner-imaging competitive SE block, which suggests that it may belong to the sub-category cs.MM (Multimedia). The proposed mechanism involves modeling channel-wise relations, which is a common theme in machine learning and artificial intelligence, suggesting that it may also belong to the sub-categories cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper involves carrying out experiments on datasets, which suggests that it may also belong to the sub-category cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
